Then $|f(a)-a|$ is the vertical distance from the green to the red graph at $x=a$. We can see that this distance varies from $0$ to $1$, inclusive of $0$ but not of $1$ (since the hollow dots on the graph of $y=f(x)$ represent points which are not part of the graph). Since $f(x)\le x$ for all $x$, we see that $f(x)-x$ is zero or negative, and its range is $\boxed{(-1,0]}$.
#### (-1,0]

Note that $\frac{2n-4}{2-n} = \frac{2(n-2)}{-(n-2)}=-2$.  From this, we can rewrite the given equation and solve: \begin{align*}
\frac{2-n}{n+1}-2&=1\\
\Rightarrow \qquad \frac{2-n}{n+1}&=3\\
\Rightarrow \qquad 2-n&=3n+3\\
\Rightarrow \qquad -1&=4n\\
\Rightarrow \qquad \boxed{-\frac{1}{4}}&=n
\end{align*}
#### -\frac{1}{4}

Because the three points are on the same line, the slope between the first and second equals the slope between the first and the third.  This gives us the equation: \begin{align*}
\frac{3-(-5)}{(-a+2) -3} &= \frac{2- (-5)}{(2a+3) - 3} \\
\frac{8}{-a-1} &= \frac{7}{2a} \\
8(2a) &= 7(-a-1) \\
23a &= -7 \\
&a = \boxed{\frac{-7}{23}}.
\end{align*}
#### \frac{-7}{23}

